        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-08-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1678" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1678">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.267/8–1649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-16">August 16,
                            1949.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 16—11:13 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 967. As we envisaged, story on closure Canton Consulate General has
                    reached press and we of necessity have confirmed closure but have made no
                    comment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
